com.android.test.runner.listener

Class InstrumentationResultPrinter

  • java.lang.Object
    • RunListener
      • com.android.test.runner.listener.InstrumentationRunListener
        • com.android.test.runner.listener.InstrumentationResultPrinter

  • public class InstrumentationResultPrinter
extends InstrumentationRunListener
    A RunListener that sends detailed pass/fail results back as instrumentation status bundles. This output appears when running the instrumentation in '-r' or raw mode.

      • REPORT_VALUE_ID

        public static final java.lang.String REPORT_VALUE_ID
        This value, if stored with key Instrumentation.REPORT_KEY_IDENTIFIER, identifies AndroidJUnitRunner as the source of the report. This is sent with all status messages.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • REPORT_KEY_NUM_TOTAL

        public static final java.lang.String REPORT_KEY_NUM_TOTAL
        If included in the status or final bundle sent to an IInstrumentationWatcher, this key identifies the total number of tests that are being run. This is sent with all status messages.

      • REPORT_KEY_NUM_CURRENT

        public static final java.lang.String REPORT_KEY_NUM_CURRENT
        If included in the status or final bundle sent to an IInstrumentationWatcher, this key identifies the sequence number of the current test. This is sent with any status message describing a specific test being started or completed.
